description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered and Student Nurse Online recruitment event&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tuesday 24 November, 3 - 4.30pm, MS Teams&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will take place the following week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Nursing information events are designed to help you get answers to all your questions, whether you are a &lt;strong&gt;Registered Nurse, Student Nurse (qualifying in 2021) or Nurse&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;returning to practice&lt;/strong&gt;. You can:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ask our friendly Senior Nurses what it is like to be a nurse at HDFT;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;hear about the training and development opportunities we have, including our &lt;em&gt;2-year Preceptorship programme;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;find out about the range of roles on offer at Harrogate District Hospital.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The event will take place on Tuesday 24 November, 3-4.30pm via MS Teams. You can ask questions and we will answer them live.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to book&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to attend the event and book an interview, please click the green ‘Apply for this job’ button. Interviews will take place a week after the event. Your interview time and date will be confirmed by email.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would prefer to attend the&lt;strong&gt; online event&lt;/strong&gt; first and apply later, then please book your place in advance via email&lt;strong&gt;, Emily.reid11@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt; or telephone, &lt;strong&gt;01423 554429&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This event will provide you with the information you need to take the next step towards becoming a Registered Nurse at Harrogate and District NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a Trust we offer our Registered Nurses:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to clinical skills training in our Clinical Skills Lab and personal development courses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First Line Leadership programme to help develop your leadership skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly recommended two-year Preceptorship Programme and your first year of NMC fees paid&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4 weeks supernumerary and ongoing mentoring&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Band 6 and 7 development posts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and guidance with revalidation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Harrogate and District NHS Foundation Trust we provide ‘outstanding’ care to both our patients and our staff. We support staff through benefits, health and wellbeing initiatives and opportunities for personal and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An inclusive and supportive culture – our Trust encourages staff to bring their whole selves to work and active Staff Networks identify areas for improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff Recognition - as well as regular appraisals, we recognise staff with our Making a Difference and Team of the Month Awards plus the Christmas Oscars.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Support and wellbeing - we have a comprehensive Employee Assistance Programme, counselling service and fast track physiotherapy service for employees.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff Benefits - We have a range of staff benefits and schemes to support staff health, engagement, wellbeing and inclusion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Harrogate is consistently voted the happiest place to live in the UK, with a vibrant local music, arts and foodie scene. Beautiful natural spaces, sports facilities, great shopping and high performing schools make this a great location to settle down in.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at Harrogate and District NHS Foundation Trust follow us on Facebook: ‘Team HDFT jobs – Harrogate and District NHS Foundation Trust’ and Twitter: @HDFT_Careers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameEmily ReidJob titleResourcing Project ManagerEmail addressemily.reid11@nhs.netTelephone number01423 554429&lt;/p&gt;
